1
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:12,100
<i>It feels like
I'm not even your real child!</i>

2
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:13,600
<i>I'm sure
your dad was just shocked.</i>

3
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:15,067
<i>- That's why he said that.
- No, Mom.</i>

4
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,667
<i>He was very clear.
He wants me out of this house.</i>

5
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,800
<i>Let's call
our newly engaged couple,</i>

6
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:20,900
<i> Paolo and Marj.</i>

7
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:23,367
<i>You shouldn't have agreed
to marry Paolo.</i>

8
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,433
<i>You know they keep fighting
because of you.</i>

9
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:28,000
<i> That was never my intention.</i>

10
00:00:28,133 --> 00:00:32,900
<i>Get ready to be miserable
in my house, Marj.</i>

11
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>Marj Castillo is marrying
your brother?</i>

12
00:00:35,367 --> 00:00:36,667
<i>- You know her?
- Of course.</i>

13
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,933
<i>So she's going to be
a Torrecampo now.</i>

14
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:41,367
<i>Maybe getting married
is a mistake.</i>

15
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,567
<i> He'll move on from you.</i>

16
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,400
<i>Especially once he meets
someone else.</i>

17
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:47,600
<i>We actually have a lot
in common, don't we?</i>

18
00:00:47,733 --> 00:00:52,567
<i>Want to take this
somewhere quieter?</i>

19
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,733
<i> You're still pretty hands-on.</i>

20
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:56,000
<i> Mom.</i>

21
00:00:56,133 --> 00:00:59,667
<i>Marj, maybe you can help
your mom pack the leftovers?</i>

22
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,700
<i>It'd be a waste.
Every bit counts.</i>

23
00:01:01,833 --> 00:01:03,667
<i> Even a little class.</i>

24
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,633
Oscar's on his way here.

25
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:12,333
He's with Jobert.

26
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:13,933
Looks like he found himself
a new best friend.

27
00:01:14,067 --> 00:01:17,267
Oh boy, that one
won't shut up later.

28
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:20,700
Excuse me.

29
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:25,733
Oh, it's dad.

30
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:30,600
Mr. Jacinto's heading home.

31
00:01:30,733 --> 00:01:33,667
I'll just say goodbye real
quick, okay? I'll be right back.

32
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:44,100
Sweetheart.

33
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:46,133
If you ask me...

34
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:51,600
I don't really mind
who you marry, Marj.

35
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:53,067
What I didn't like

36
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,800
was how I felt after talking
to his mom earlier.

37
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:01,367
It's scarier when...

38
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,700
someone acts nice...

39
00:02:05,867 --> 00:02:09,967
but you don't realize they're
already looking down on you.

40
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,200
Mom, please just bear
with Paolo's mom.

41
00:02:15,367 --> 00:02:17,600
She just has really
high standards.

42
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:20,100
But they say she's nice.

43
00:02:20,233 --> 00:02:23,033
Paolo's dad is nice, too.

44
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:26,467
Strict, but down-to-earth.

45
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:30,933
And Jobert and I are really
welcome in this house.

46
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:33,667
He's very concerned
about my brother.

47
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:37,067
Maybe this is just
the adjustment phase.

48
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:38,967
We just need to get used to it.

49
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:44,567
And since Sir Greg
believes Paolo really loves me,

50
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,133
I know I can handle this.

51
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:49,733
Marj...

52
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:51,733
sweetheart, there's still time.

53
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:57,233
Just make sure you're making
the right choice.

54
00:02:57,367 --> 00:03:03,467
Mom, this is my first chance
to be part of a new family.

55
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:08,567
You know what happened
to my old one.

56
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:10,100
Our dad abandoned Jobert and me.

57
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:14,833
Thank you for worrying,

58
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:17,333
but I won't change my mind.

59
00:03:17,467 --> 00:03:19,800
Always remember, dear.

60
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:23,667
You don't have to put up
with anyone.

61
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:30,833
Then why did you, Mom?

62
00:03:30,967 --> 00:03:34,567
Even when dad treated you badly,
you stayed.

63
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:41,700
I wish you'd follow
your own advice.

64
00:04:07,467 --> 00:04:09,233
Marj!

65
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:13,367
I went with Oscar in the car.

66
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:16,867
Mom.

67
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,167
- Jobert.
- Take care.

68
00:04:18,300 --> 00:04:20,933
Oscar! Bye-bye.

69
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,767
- We'll get going.
- Thank you, Oscar.

70
00:04:42,933 --> 00:04:45,200
Bye!

71
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,967
Can you believe that?

72
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:46,900
You almost hooked up

73
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:51,000
with Edward Torrecampo
of Torrecampo Realty!

74
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:52,867
You're driving me nuts!

75
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,400
But let's be real, your looks
didn't get you anywhere.

76
00:05:56,533 --> 00:05:57,900
He didn't bite.

77
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:01,167
Not yet.

78
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:02,700
Baby steps, Lalaine.

79
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:05,000
I already showed him
the showroom.

80
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:07,267
We're at the reservation stage.

81
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,233
And I'm sure
this isn't just a site visit.

82
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,533
Yeah, but it's still
just a reservation fee.

83
00:06:13,667 --> 00:06:16,967
Meanwhile, Marj Castillo's
marrying his brother.

84
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,667
So what?

85
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,533
She's just one unit.

86
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:24,367
I'm going for the penthouse.

87
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:27,733
Edward himself
is prime property.

88
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,233
I hit the jackpot.

89
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:34,867
I'll finally escape my debts
and the gossip back in Batangas.

90
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:35,933
And,

91
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:38,167
I'm tired of pretending
I'm rich.

92
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,467
Especially when credit card
interest is drowning me.

93
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,767
You should've just looked
for a sugar daddy.

94
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:46,133
Not a Torrecampo.

95
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:48,867
Excuse me.
I'm done with that job.

96
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,200
I've leveled up to Edward.

97
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:53,200
Single. Legit.

98
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,133
From a good family.

99
00:06:56,933 --> 00:07:00,133
Once I'm Mrs. Torrecampo,

100
00:07:01,733 --> 00:07:04,467
I'll be rich again for real.

101
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,100
Not just in name.

102
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:09,133
No collectors.

103
00:07:09,267 --> 00:07:12,067
No shame to swallow.

104
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:15,800
But can you handle Marjorie
Castillo as your sister-in-law?

105
00:07:15,967 --> 00:07:18,967
<i>Funny, isn't it?
This is like the same as before.</i>

106
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:24,033
You were rivals at work,
now even in the family.

107
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:26,467
And she beat you to it.

108
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,700
For now,
she only got the brother.

109
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:35,600
But I'll win over
the entire Torrecampo clan.

110
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,500
Edward is my way in.

111
00:07:38,633 --> 00:07:40,433
Once I'm inside,

112
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:42,633
good luck to Marj.

113
00:07:42,767 --> 00:07:47,100
I'll terminate her contract
with the Torrecampos.

114
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,567
<i>Your father must be proud
of you.</i>

115
00:08:22,033 --> 00:08:23,400
<i> I'm impressed, Villareal.</i>

116
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:27,600
<i> A real businessman indeed.</i>

117
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,500
<i>Is this really your collateral?</i>

118
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:36,333
<i>Your debt is cleared.
We're even.</i>

119
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,033
<i> Dad...</i>

120
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:41,367
<i>We talked about this, didn't we?</i>

121
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:43,767
<i>Why did you say you'd leave me?</i>

122
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:49,333
<i>Sweetheart, this is the only
way. We have no other choice.</i>

123
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,667
<i> Relax, baby girl.</i>

124
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,967
<i> This is just business.</i>

125
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:57,433
<i> You won't lose anything...</i>

126
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,367
<i> if you just play along.</i>

127
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,133
<i> Just playtime.</i>

128
00:09:01,267 --> 00:09:02,600
<i> Playtime.</i>

129
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:04,233
<i> Caleb! Basti!</i>

130
00:09:04,367 --> 00:09:06,233
<i> Escort our guest out.</i>

131
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:08,167
<i> Dad, please!</i>

132
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,567
<i> Where are you taking my dad?</i>

133
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:13,167
<i>Dad, don't leave!
I don't want this!</i>

134
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:15,767
<i>- Relax!
- Dad, don't leave me!</i>

135
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:22,933
<i> Dad!</i>

136
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:28,900
You won't lose anything...

137
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:30,900
if you know how to play.

138
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,833
I won't be a debt payment
anymore.

139
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:43,367
I won't be collateral.

140
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,900
Or a toy.

141
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,833
I'll be the one who plays.

142
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,667
And I'll be the one who wins.

143
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:23,300
I have to win.

144
00:10:26,467 --> 00:10:30,167
Why did you choose to meet here?

145
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,900
We've been meeting
at restaurants and cafes

146
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:35,067
for months.

147
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:36,633
Let's change it up.

148
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,367
<i> Be careful, kids!</i>

149
00:10:52,367 --> 00:10:54,367
Just let them have fun.

150
00:11:00,467 --> 00:11:02,700
You miss your family, don't you?

151
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,233
Why don't you go back home?

152
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:08,667
What for?

153
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:10,700
So dad and I can fight again?

154
00:11:11,733 --> 00:11:13,633
No, thanks.

155
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:15,033
I'm fine here.

156
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:19,300
What about your mom?

157
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:20,833
Can you really leave her?

158
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:24,833
I'm sure she misses you so much.

159
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:29,600
And don't worry yet
about fighting with your dad.

160
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:39,500
Didn't you say you're better
at business than your brother?

161
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:41,433
Then prove it.

162
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:45,067
Don't let your brother
outshine you.

163
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:49,367
Earn your place in your family
and the company.

164
00:11:52,733 --> 00:11:54,167
You really think so?

165
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:57,033
I don't just think it.

166
00:11:58,133 --> 00:11:59,500
I know.

167
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:03,333
You're the one people
should look up to.

168
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,600
Maybe you just need someone

169
00:12:06,733 --> 00:12:10,967
who sees how capable
you really are.

170
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:15,300
And who you can become with
the right person beside you.

171
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:18,300
Can you do it?

172
00:12:50,167 --> 00:12:51,633
Hello.

173
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:53,000
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi.

174
00:12:53,133 --> 00:12:55,200
- Oh, hi, Mrs. Torrecampo.
- Hi. Nice to see you again.

175
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:56,467
Nice to see you, too.

176
00:13:00,367 --> 00:13:02,633
But Marj told me you were with
the outreach program today.

177
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,267
She said you couldn't make it.

178
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,967
Yeah, but I left early.

179
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:08,433
I wanted to oversee
the gown fitting.

180
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:11,767
I figured if I left
the decisions to others,

181
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:14,567
this wedding might turn
into a disaster.

182
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:17,833
Mom, thank you so much.

183
00:13:17,967 --> 00:13:20,567
I know you're very busy,

184
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:22,633
but you still arranged this
meeting with Julius

185
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:24,600
here at your home.

186
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:31,033
So, you picked the flowers, the
theme, and the invitation paper?

187
00:13:31,167 --> 00:13:32,733
Yes, Mom.

188
00:13:32,867 --> 00:13:36,300
Paolo told me orchids
are your favorite.

189
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:37,500
That's why I chose them.

190
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,000
Good.

191
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:44,767
Not bad. Looks like you can
follow directions after all.

192
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,733
You do have taste...

193
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:50,167
when you're properly guided.

194
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,633
May I see the designs?

195
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,667
Oh, okay.

196
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,567
You know, I just want
everything to be appropriate.

197
00:13:57,700 --> 00:14:00,667
After all,
this is a Torrecampo wedding.

198
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:04,967
It needs to be elegant,
but sincere.

199
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:07,400
Not simple in a cheap way.

200
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:13,900
Mom, these were based on
your suggestions, right?

201
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,233
Yes, but now that I see it
on paper...

202
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:20,800
I don't think...

203
00:14:21,933 --> 00:14:24,133
I don't think
it'll look good on you.

204
00:14:24,267 --> 00:14:26,867
It just doesn't suit you.

205
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:30,967
Nothing personal.
I'm sure you understand.

206
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,900
You know what?

207
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:34,967
Let's rework the gown.

208
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:37,300
Change the fabric,
change the neckline,

209
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:38,867
let's change the bride.

210
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:42,500
Just kidding.

211
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:44,600
Come on.

212
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:46,533
Can you show me
the other designs?

213
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:50,733
I think this one could work.

214
00:15:03,500 --> 00:15:04,900
<i> Thea?</i>

215
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:07,633
<i> Thea?</i>

216
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,800
<i> Thea.</i>

217
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,067
Wakey, wakey.

218
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,500
Good morning.

219
00:15:47,633 --> 00:15:49,067
Morning.

220
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:51,067
Good morning, Edward.

221
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:54,067
I made you breakfast.

222
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,733
Want coffee?

223
00:15:55,867 --> 00:15:57,700
Two shots, one sugar.

224
00:15:57,833 --> 00:16:00,167
Wow. You've got it memorized.

225
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,867
You know...

226
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,800
we've been like this
for months now.

227
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:08,467
Coffee. Takeouts.

228
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:10,533
You're the only one
taking care of me.

229
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:13,433
I might get used to this.

230
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:26,967
Oh no.

231
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:29,633
Why?

232
00:16:31,067 --> 00:16:33,867
My landlord just texted me.

233
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,200
There's a problem
with my condo.

234
00:16:37,333 --> 00:16:38,833
The ceiling's leaking.

235
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,233
What are you supposed to do?
How will you go home?

236
00:16:46,167 --> 00:16:48,033
I might stay with my aunt
for now.

237
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:53,400
But she's super strict
and always cranky.

238
00:16:53,533 --> 00:16:54,933
And she lives really far.

239
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:59,433
Most of my clients
are around here, too.

240
00:17:01,633 --> 00:17:03,067
Then...

241
00:17:04,533 --> 00:17:05,967
stay here for now.

242
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,667
Are you serious?

243
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,667
I don't want to be a burden.

244
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:14,533
Of course.

245
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,567
We're already together here all
the time anyway. It's just us.

246
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:23,633
And you're the only one I want
to have coffee and takeout with.

247
00:17:25,067 --> 00:17:30,033
And make chaos with,
morning, noon, and night.

248
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:35,333
I don't want to change anything.

249
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:39,200
You're stuck with me.

250
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:45,233
So...

251
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:47,733
we're exclusive now?

252
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,767
I'm your girlfriend?

253
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:53,133
You could've at least told me.

254
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:56,233
Why?

255
00:17:56,367 --> 00:17:57,300
Aren't we already dating?

256
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,033
Isn't it obvious?

257
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:01,167
What do you want?

258
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:04,533
A grand launch party?

259
00:18:13,433 --> 00:18:17,667
So if we're exclusive,

260
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:20,167
I'm your plus-one, right?

261
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,133
I'm not attending that.

262
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,400
Why not?

263
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:36,933
Don't you want to introduce me
to your family?

264
00:18:38,467 --> 00:18:40,400
Aren't you proud of me?

265
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:44,933
And didn't we already
talk about this?

266
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:48,767
Don't isolate yourself
from your family.

267
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:54,600
They need you
because you're capable.

268
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,133
You're reliable.

269
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:00,833
You're such a smooth talker.

270
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:05,267
You always make me feel...

271
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,833
like I can do anything.

272
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:11,933
What are you, a life coach...

273
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,067
or a girlfriend?

274
00:19:15,033 --> 00:19:16,400
Girlfriend.

275
00:19:16,533 --> 00:19:17,533
Life coach.

276
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:21,300
Depends on which package
you want.

277
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,833
Anything is possible,

278
00:19:25,933 --> 00:19:27,333
as long as I'm with you.

279
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:40,733
<i>Paolo asked me
to give this to you.</i>

280
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:44,800
He's so sweet.

281
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,400
Really sweet.

282
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:57,033
Oh, there's an engraving
on the back.

283
00:19:57,167 --> 00:19:59,367
For every home we'll build,

284
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,933
for every storm we'll survive.

285
00:20:03,100 --> 00:20:04,467
We can do this.

286
00:20:06,667 --> 00:20:11,100
Looks like my future
daughter-in-law is almost ready.

287
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:15,167
Can you give us a moment?

288
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,767
Yes.

289
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:38,700
Oh, Marjorie...

290
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:40,733
I have to hand it to you.

291
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:43,633
You've endured quite
a lot to get here.

292
00:20:45,533 --> 00:20:47,667
And yet here you are,

293
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:51,367
calm, composed, radiant.

294
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:55,867
But you know,
you still have time.

295
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:00,133
To change your mind.

296
00:21:02,033 --> 00:21:05,133
Why would I do that?

297
00:21:05,267 --> 00:21:06,967
Everything's ready.

298
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:08,633
Exactly.

299
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,633
Everything is ready.

300
00:21:10,767 --> 00:21:12,467
Maybe except you.

301
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:19,333
You know, Marjorie,

302
00:21:21,633 --> 00:21:25,300
if you think this wedding will
make you part of our family,

303
00:21:26,767 --> 00:21:29,000
<i> you're wrong.</i>

304
00:21:29,133 --> 00:21:31,767
<i> You can still walk away...</i>

305
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,233
while you still have
your dignity.

306
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:36,533
And don't worry
about the expenses.

307
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:41,033
They're nothing compared to the
cost of my family's peace

308
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:43,867
if someone who doesn't belong
gets in.

309
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:54,000
So, Marjorie,

310
00:21:56,333 --> 00:22:03,200
are you sure
this is what you really want?

311
00:22:08,733 --> 00:22:10,500
Okay, then.

312
00:22:10,633 --> 00:22:13,733
Let's go. We shouldn't keep
the guests waiting.

313
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,300
The entourage is ready.
Has the bride arrived?

314
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:38,767
Yes, the bride is here.

315
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:40,767
I'll tell her to stand by.

316
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:44,267
Okay. Please get ready.

317
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,733
Please fix yourselves up.

318
00:22:52,167 --> 00:22:53,167
Excuse me.

319
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:55,033
Let's stay on standby, okay?
I'll be right back.

320
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:02,867
Marj...

321
00:23:04,067 --> 00:23:07,733
Everyone's happy.

322
00:23:07,867 --> 00:23:10,600
Why aren't you?

323
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:14,167
How can you tell?

324
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:17,067
I can see it in your eyes.

325
00:23:18,233 --> 00:23:20,600
When a smile's fake,

326
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:24,200
the eyes don't move.

327
00:23:24,333 --> 00:23:27,567
When it's real,

328
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:30,367
the whole face lights up.

329
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:33,800
Yours doesn't light up, Marj.

330
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:36,367
Why are you sad?

331
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:40,233
Aren't you finally going
to be with Paolo?

332
00:23:46,467 --> 00:23:48,333
Jobert...

333
00:23:48,467 --> 00:23:51,067
what if we just leave?

334
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,433
Just us again.

335
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:55,900
Let's go back home.

336
00:24:15,833 --> 00:24:18,433
<i> What about Paolo?</i>

337
00:24:18,567 --> 00:24:21,200
If you're not there,

338
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:23,567
he will be sad.

339
00:24:34,267 --> 00:24:38,567
If Paolo is sad,
I'll be sad, too.

340
00:24:38,700 --> 00:24:40,567
I don't want to be sad.

341
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,900
I'm scared.

342
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:47,833
It feels like
I don't want this anymore.

343
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:53,667
<i> Sometimes I get scared, too.</i>

344
00:24:55,600 --> 00:25:00,400
<i>But remember
what you told me before?</i>

345
00:25:00,533 --> 00:25:03,333
When I'm scared,

346
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:04,833
I just breathe.

347
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,033
Now, Marj...

348
00:25:07,167 --> 00:25:09,900
it's your turn to breathe.

349
00:25:23,767 --> 00:25:25,633
<i> Marj...</i>

350
00:25:25,767 --> 00:25:28,467
<i> I have a wish.</i>

351
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:32,400
I hope you'll be happy.

352
00:25:32,533 --> 00:25:36,233
That your face will light up.

353
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:39,233
Because if you're happy,

354
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:41,667
Paolo will be happy, too.

355
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:44,067
And I will also be happy.

356
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:00,733
What's taking her so long?

357
00:26:00,867 --> 00:26:03,067
Chill, Bro. Just relax.

358
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:06,667
Regina,

359
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,467
does this have anything
to do with you?

360
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,967
I didn't do anything, okay?

361
00:26:30,733 --> 00:26:31,700
Sir, excuse me.

362
00:26:31,833 --> 00:26:33,100
There's been a bit of a delay.

363
00:26:33,233 --> 00:26:34,167
Where is she?

364
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:36,467
She was on standby earlier
in the bridal car.

365
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:37,900
But then she suddenly
disappeared.

366
00:26:38,033 --> 00:26:40,000
I know you didn't want
this to happen, Mom,

367
00:26:40,133 --> 00:26:41,867
but I'm hurt too.

368
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,100
A lot of people saw it.

369
00:26:43,267 --> 00:26:44,467
It's not just me
who was humiliated.

370
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,333
Paolo's whole family was, too.

371
00:26:46,467 --> 00:26:47,767
I'm sorry.

372
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:48,800
Marj.

373
00:26:48,933 --> 00:26:49,833
Why are you here?

374
00:26:49,967 --> 00:26:51,500
Can we just put it behind us?

375
00:26:51,633 --> 00:26:53,433
Maybe he really has changed.

376
00:26:53,567 --> 00:26:57,133
Maybe this is the right time,
sweetheart, to forgive.

377
00:26:57,267 --> 00:26:59,233
To finally fix things.

378
00:26:59,367 --> 00:27:02,600
Some people don't deserve
a second chance.

379
00:27:02,733 --> 00:27:03,567
Marj's unbelievable, right?

380
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:05,600
You're humbling yourself,

381
00:27:05,733 --> 00:27:07,633
yet somehow
you're still the bad guy.

382
00:27:07,767 --> 00:27:12,000
Enjoy the spotlight
while it lasts, Mrs. Torrecampo.
